message: init
Right, that's the first quater done
Adds element
Change lint rules to AirBnB
Session storage used to save tile collapse state
Disables ESlint for mansory file
Adds icons for networking services
Removed non-essential dependencies
Adds YAML loader
Uses SVGs instead of images for interface icons
Removed Element UI, and replaced usage with vanilla stuff
Show opening method on hover. Allow items to be opened in an iframe
Removed SCSS variables, and replaced with CSS --vars
Streamlined dependencies
Deoendency update
Things and Stuff
Displays a tab view in the config modal, with raw YAML for downloading
Adds JSON editor component in config modal
Shows toast on success, and other UX improvments
Adds backup functionality
Adds sytnax highlighting to the YAML export
Adds code editor for user to specify custom CSS
Improved the Docker deployment process, plus switched to a new Apline image
Adds license to package.json, updates Docker docs
Calls config validator when serve starts, and adds documentation in readme
Implemented config validation into the JSON editor
Removes explicit use of Ajv. Fixes #17
Implements docker container healthchecks
Fixed lint errors caused by octal character, and added missing yaml dependency
Adds git hook to check files prior to commit
Adds Heroku support
Adds support for Netlify 1-Click deployment, adds main script to package.json, updates name and adds docs
Removes engine from packages.json, to fix Netlify build. Updates deployment docs
Gernal refactoring
Adds server endpoint for backing up and saving conf.yml. Still needs some improvments though.

:building_construction: Sets environment in Docker, and adds recompile watcher to start script

Ensures environment is correctly set to production, and sets build-and-start script to now recompoile when conf.yml is updated
